<div class="blurb" role="region" aria-labelledby="dependencies-title">
    <div class="header">
        <h1 id="dependencies-title">Dependencies</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Asimov depends on the following Python packages:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <a href="https://github.com/letmaik/pyvirtualcam" rel="noopener noreferrer" 
                   aria-label="pyvirtualcam home page">pyvirtualcam</a> — Sends frames to a virtual camera.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://pypi.org/project/opencv-python/" rel="noopener noreferrer" 
                   aria-label="opencv-python home page">opencv-python</a> — Python bindings for OpenCV for computer vision tasks.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://numpy.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer" 
                   aria-label="numpy home page">numpy</a> — Fundamental package for scientific computing.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://developers.google.com/mediapipe" rel="noopener noreferrer" 
                   aria-label="mediapipe home page">mediapipe</a> — Cross-platform framework for building multimodal applied ML pipelines.
            </li>
            <li>
                <a href="https://pypi.org/project/PyQt5/" rel="noopener noreferrer" 
                   aria-label="PyQt5 home page">PyQt5</a> — Python bindings for the Qt GUI framework.
            </li>
        </ul>

        <p>And the following system packages should be installed via <code>dnf</code> on Fedora:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="https://ffmpeg.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="ffmpeg home page"><code>ffmpeg</code></a> — for video encoding and decoding (optional).</li>
            <li><code>gstreamer1-plugins-base</code> — base GStreamer plugins (optional).</li>
            <li><code>gstreamer1-plugins-good</code> — additional “good” GStreamer plugins (optional).</li>
            <li><a href="https://mesa3d.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Mesa home page"><code>mesa-libGL</code></a> — OpenGL library for rendering.</li>
            <li><code>qt5-qtbase</code> — Qt5 base libraries for GUI support.</li>
            <li><a href="https://opencv.org/" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="OpenCV home page"><code>opencv</code></a> — OpenCV system libraries.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Please make sure all Python and required system dependencies are installed before running Asimov.</p>
    </div>
</div>
